<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    
    <!-- The page supports both dark and light color schemes,
         and the page author prefers / default is light. -->
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="dark light">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/bootstrap_dark.css">



    <title>FilePush</title>
</head>
<body>
    
    <div class="container" style="margin-top: 16px;">
        <div class="row text-center">
            <h1>FilePush Client</h1>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container text-center" style="margin-top: 32px; padding-left: 10vw; padding-right: 10vw;">
        
        <div class="row text-start">
            <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                To get started download the FilePush client below
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="row text-center" style="padding-left: 20vw; padding-right: 20vw; margin-bottom: 16px;">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-block" href="/static/client.exe" download> Download FilePush Client</a>
        </div>

        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                Once the file has finished downloading run it to start the first time setup.
                You will be prompted to enter your information.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                After finishing the setup the FilePush Client will begin running.
                While FilePush Client is running, any files added under your FilePush
                Account will be automatically downloaded to your computer.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="row text-start">
            <h3>Running at boot</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                To have FilePush Client run in the background whenver your computer is turned on,
                start by storing the FilePush Client executable in a standard location such as
                program files.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                Then create a shortcut to the FilePush Client by right clicking on <code>client.exe</code> and
                selecting create shortcut.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                After creating a shortcut open the run application either by pressing
                the windows key and searching <code>run</code> or pressing <code>&lt;Winows Key&gt; + R</code>.
                Then type <code>shell:startup</code>.
            </p>
        </div>
         <div class="row text-start">
            <p>
                This will open the startup folder, from here drag the shortcut you created earlier into the startup
                folder, from here FilePush Client will run in the background on boot.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    


</body>
</html>





